<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL&#174; VT 365 DIESEL ENGINE - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVE TRAIN - Cleaning and Inspection - Rocker
        Arm Carrier Fulcrum Removal
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="12">
        <title>Rocker Arm Carrier Fulcrum Removal</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Disassembly of Rocker Fulcrums</title>
            <figure id="f2350467" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD08/D08166.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 175. Removal of bolts from dual rocker arm fulcrum</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Intake fulcrum plate</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Mounting bolt and spacer (8 each)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Dual rocker fulcrum plate (3)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust fulcrum plate</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove eight M8 x 65 bolts and spacers holding rocker arm fulcrums to the rocker arm
                    carrier.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove - as assemblies - the intake fulcrum plate, three dual rocker fulcrum plates, and
                    exhaust fulcrum plate from the rocker arm carrier. Do steps 3 through 6 to disassemble.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figD08/D08168.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Separation of rocker arm from fulcrum plate (typical)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker arm</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fulcrum plate</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker arm clip</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Put rocker arm and fulcrum plate assembly upside down in your palm.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Push up on the rocker arm with palm and forward on the fulcrum plate with thumb of
                    opposite hand.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figD08/D08167.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Rocker arm separated (typical)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker arm ball</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker arm</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker arm clip</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fulcrum plate</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the rocker arm and rocker arm ball.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figd06/D0684.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Rocker arm clip removed (typical)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fulcrum plate</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker arm clip</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove and discard rocker arm clip.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figD08/D08235.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="592px" box="no"/>
                <caption>New rocker arm fulcrum (dual)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust end</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">intake end</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Earlier rocker arm fulcrums are no longer serviceable; new rocker arm fulcrums and clips are
                        required.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Cleaning and Inspection</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, wear safety glasses with side shields to protect eyes.
                        Limit compressed air pressure to 207 kPa (30 psi).
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean all parts with a suitable solvent. Use filtered compressed air to dry parts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect each rocker arm pivot foot and corresponding valve bridge for pitting or
                    scuffing. Inspect each rocker arm ball and socket for scuffing. Replace rocker arms and valve
                    bridges as required.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect rocker arm post ball socket for excessive wear. Inspect bolts for thread damage,
                    replace worn components as required.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect the valve cover gasket for any evidence of damage or misalignment under
                    compression. Under normal service conditions it is designed to be reused.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Reassembly</title>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figD08/D08235.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="592px" box="no"/>
                <caption>New rocker arm fulcrum (dual underside)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust end</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">intake end</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Earlier rocker arm fulcrums are no longer serviceable; new rocker arm fulcrums and clips are
                        required.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figd06/D0684.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installation of new rocker arm clip (typical)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fulcrum plate</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker arm clip</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new rocker arm clip on new fulcrum plate.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD08/D08167.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 176. Installation of rocker arm ball (typical)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker arm ball</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker arm</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker arm clip</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fulcrum plate</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert rocker arm ball in detent in fulcrum plate.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD08/D08234.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 177. Installation of rocker arm (typical)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker arm</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fulcrum plate</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker arm clip</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position lower part of rocker arm under rocker arm clip, push up with your palm, and use
                    thumb back to pull upper part of rocker arm over rocker arm ball.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check for freedom of movement of rocker arm on fulcrum plate.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650481" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd08/D08104.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 178. Installation of end fulcrum plate and dowel</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Assemble individual intake and exhaust fulcrum plates to each end of the rocker carrier
                    assembly by setting the fulcrum onto the locating dowel and orienting the stamped
                    <emph type="bold">E</emph>
                    and
                    <emph type="bold">I</emph>
                    to face up. Install an M8 x 65 bolt and spacer onto each fulcrum and tighten to the special torque .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650482" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd08/D0830.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 179. Installation of dual rocker fulcrum plates</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Assemble the dual rocker fulcrum plates to carrier assembly by orienting the
                    <emph type="bold">E</emph>
                    and
                    <emph type="bold">I</emph>
                    facing up and the casting branches towards the camshaft. Install six M8 x 65 bolts and spacers and
                    tighten to the special torque .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650483" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd08/D0836.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 180. Cylinder head to rocker carrier gasket</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replace cylinder head to rocker carrier gasket.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
